ants-terminal (0.7.21-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Lua sandbox hardening trio from the 0.7.12 /indie-review.
    Three small defense-in-depth fixes in LuaEngine, all locked
    by a behavioral + source-grep regression test
    (tests/features/lua_sandbox_hardening).
  * Security: string.dump removed from the plugin sandbox.
    Lua 5.4 has no bytecode verifier — string.dump(f) returns
    bytecode that a crafted loader call could execute. Closed
    at the sandbox layer via lua_setfield on the string table,
    independent of the already-nilled load/loadstring/loadfile.
  * Security: LuaEngine::loadScript forces "t" (text-only) load
    mode. Replaced luaL_dofile (which forwards with mode=nullptr,
    accepting both text and binary chunks) with luaL_loadfilex(...,
    "t") + lua_pcall. Adds a second rejection gate at the Lua
    loader level alongside the existing 0x1b first-byte peek.
  * Security: instruction-count hook cleared before lua_close in
    shutdown. Closes the UAF window where __gc metamethods
    running during close could observe a partially-finalized
    engine via the hook's __ants_engine registry lookup.

