ants-terminal (0.7.20-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Tier 2 hardening sweep — three open items from the 0.7.12
    /indie-review landed as one release. Each fix has a behavioral
    regression test and was verified to fail against pre-fix source
    via git-stash before locking. All 71 fast tests green.
  * Security: debug.log lands 0600 regardless of umask. The log can
    include PTY keystrokes, AI endpoint bodies, OSC 133 HMAC
    material, and Claude transcript parse state — none of which may
    be world-readable. DebugLog::setActive now calls
    setOwnerOnlyPerms on both the opened QFileDevice and the path
    string immediately after open, narrowing any pre-existing 0644
    file that append reused from a prior build. Uses the
    secureio.h helper, not a raw setPermissions bitmask. Locked by
    tests/features/debuglog_perms (4 invariants).
  * Security: audit path-traversal guard on finding file fields.
    User-supplied audit rules can produce Finding::file values
    like ../../etc/passwd; pre-fix, six AuditDialog call sites
    concatenated m_projectPath with the raw field and passed the
    result to snippet preview, comment classifier, inline-suppress
    scan, and the AI-triage POST body — a CWE-22 + OWASP-LLM06
    exfiltration chain via the configured chat-completions
    endpoint. New AuditDialog::resolveProjectPath helper
    canonicalizes (resolves .. and dereferences symlinks) and
    anchors the result under the canonical project root. All six
    call sites migrated. Locked by tests/features/audit_path_traversal
    (5 behavioral + source-grep invariants).
  * Fixed: Settings dialog discarded on external config reload.
    MainWindow caches the Settings dialog across opens; pre-fix,
    an external config.json edit would reload m_config but leave
    the cached dialog holding pre-reload widget state, so the next
    Save would silently overwrite the external edit.
    onConfigFileChanged now closes (if visible), deleteLater()s,
    and nulls the cached pointer so the next Preferences… open
    rebuilds from the freshly reloaded Config. Locked by
    tests/features/settings_dialog_config_reload (4 invariants).

