ants-terminal (0.7.11-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Housekeeping pass — two long-deferred 0.8+ queue items and a
    ROADMAP correction. The perf item rewrites the combining-char map
    shift in deleteChars / insertBlanks to use node-handle extract() +
    key mutate + insert() instead of rebuilding the map. The security
    item is a defence-in-depth stat-guard around the remote-control
    socket's /tmp fallback cleanup. The correction promotes the
    0.7.9-era text-run QString accumulator work from deferred to
    shipped (it was, the ROADMAP entry just missed the update).
  * Changed: combining-char map shift without rebuild. deleteChars /
    insertBlanks used to build a fresh unordered_map<int, vector
    <uint32_t>>, move each surviving entry into it (re-hashing every
    key), then move-assign it back. Rewrote to collect affected keys
    in two small local vectors (toErase / toShift), erase the deleted
    ones, then for each shift extract the node handle, mutate its
    integer key, and reinsert — zero bucket reallocation, zero
    re-hashing of the value vectors. deleteChars processes shifts in
    ascending order; insertBlanks in descending order. Empty-map
    fast-path skips the block entirely. Tests combining_on_resize and
    osc8_insert_delete_lines still pass.
  * Security: IPC-socket /tmp fallback stat-guard. RemoteControl::
    start() used to call QLocalServer::removeServer(path)
    unconditionally when listen() failed on a stale socket. The
    XDG_RUNTIME_DIR path is 0700-safe, but the /tmp/ants-terminal-
    <uid>.sock fallback lives in shared-world-writable space where a
    symlink or foreign file could trick us into unlinking something
    unrelated. Added a safeToUnlinkLocalSocket() helper that lstat()s
    the path and refuses removal unless it's an actual S_ISSOCK owned
    by getuid(). ENOENT passes through. On refusal the remote-control
    layer disables itself with a clear log message.
  * Fixed: ROADMAP accuracy — the deferred entry for per-frame QString
    construction in the text-run accumulator was actually shipped in
    0.7.9 (both TerminalWidget::paintEvent and GlRenderer::render
    accumulate codepoints into a reusable vector<char32_t> on the Run
    struct and call QString::fromUcs4(data, size) once at run-push
    time). Promoted to shipped with a retrospective write-up.

 -- Anthony Schemel <aant.schemel@gmail.com>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 08:35:31 +0200

ants-terminal (0.7.10-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Follow-through on the 0.7.9 null-result. The std::rotate scroll
    refactor was rejected because it paid for save/restore overhead
    without touching the real bottleneck — the per-scroll
    vector<Cell>(m_cols) heap allocation for the new bottom row. This
    release addresses that bottleneck directly with a small free-list
    of m_cols-sized cell buffers fed by any path that discards a row
    (scrollback eviction, scrollDown, insertLines, deleteLines) and
    drained by paths that need a fresh blank row. Steady-state scroll
    work on a full scrollback runs allocator-free.
  * Changed: TerminalGrid cell-buffer free-list. New m_freeCellBuffers
    pool (cap 4 entries) + takeBlankedCellsRow() / returnCellsRow()
    helpers. scrollUp, scrollDown, insertLines, deleteLines now recycle
    cell buffers instead of calling makeRow(m_cols, …) on every scroll.
    Scrollback pop_front salvages the evicted line's cells into the
    pool; the next scroll's new bottom row pulls from it, skipping the
    allocator entirely. resize() clears the pool. All 49 feature tests
    pass; scroll_region_rotate (shipped 0.7.9) verifies invariants held.
  * Performance: bench_vt_throughput newline_stream 5.26 → 6.09 MB/s
    (+15.8 %, median of ten-run pairs). Other corpora flat to mildly
    improved: ascii_print ~23, ansi_sgr ~16.5, utf8_cjk 8.9 (+12 %).
    First perf result validating the 0.7.9 thesis that the container
    shuffle was a red herring and the allocator was the actual hot
    spot.

