  * The 0.7.7 planned-work pass from the hardening four-dimensional
    review — every item marked as planned in ROADMAP.md's 0.7.7 section
    is now shipped. Two de-duplication refactors, three paint-path perf
    hoists, four regression feature-tests locking the 0.7.6 hardening
    fixes.
  * Added: regression coverage for the four 0.7.7 hardening fixes —
    tests/features/osc8_insert_delete_lines/ (CSI L / CSI M hyperlink
    sync invariant), tests/features/hyperlink_resize_clamp/ (shrink-
    resize clamp on the active OSC 8 start coordinates),
    tests/features/ssh_dash_host_rejected/ (the `--` argv terminator
    against CVE-2017-1000117 class hosts, 5 scenarios), and
    tests/features/image_bomb_png_header_peek/ (static source-
    inspection guard ensuring every loadFromData is peeked first).
    Each test is designed to fail on pre-fix code and pass now.
    49 feature/fast tests total.
