ants-terminal (0.7.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Shell integration + triggers minor release — rollup of the 0.6.1
    to 0.6.45 patch-release arc into the theme the 0.7 ROADMAP plotted
    out. No breaking API changes; every plugin that loaded against
    0.6.45 loads against 0.7.0. The minor bump reflects the accumulated
    theme delta since 0.6.0, not a manifest or ants.* schema break.
  * Shell integration: command blocks as first-class UI with OSC 133
    prompt/command/output grouping, Ctrl+Shift+Up / Down jumps,
    collapsible output with "... N lines hidden" summaries, a 2px
    pass/fail status stripe, and per-block context menu (Copy Command,
    Copy Output, Re-run, Fold/Unfold, Share as .cast). Asciinema
    .cast v2 recording — full-session via Ctrl+Shift+R and per-block
    via the context menu.
  * Semantic history: Ctrl-click on a path:line:col capture in
    scrollback opens the file at the cited position. CWD resolution
    via /proc/<pid>/cwd so relative paths Just Work without shell
    cooperation. Editor support covers VS Code family (code, code-
    insiders, codium), vi-family (nvim, vim), nano, Sublime, Helix,
    Micro, and JetBrains IDEs.
  * Shell-side HMAC verification for OSC 133 markers. When
    $ANTS_OSC133_KEY is set, every OSC 133 marker must carry an
    ahmac= param computed as HMAC-SHA256(key, <marker>|<promptId>
    [|<exitCode>]). Forged markers are dropped and a status-bar
    counter surfaces the count with a 5-second cooldown. Bash + zsh
    integration scripts shipped under packaging/shell-integration/.
  * Triggers + plugin events: full iTerm2-parity trigger rule set
    with an instant flag — bell, inject, run_script, notify, sound,
    command, highlight_line, highlight_text, make_hyperlink. OSC 1337
    SetUserVar with a user_var_changed event. Command-palette plugin
    registration via ants.palette.register(). New plugin events:
    command_finished, pane_focused, theme_changed,
    window_config_reloaded, user_var_changed, palette_action.
  * Performance: SIMD VT-parser scan — ground-state hot path scans
    16 bytes at a time via SSE2 (x86_64) / NEON (ARM64), emitting
    bulk Print actions for safe runs. Dedicated PTY read + VT parse
    worker thread with bounded back-pressure (<= 8 batches in flight).
    Incremental reflow on resize skips the allocation-heavy rewrap
    round-trip for standalone lines.
  * Platform — Wayland native: layer-shell Quake mode promotes the
    window to zwlr_layer_surface_v1 at LayerTop when layer-shell-
    qt6-devel is installed; XCB path preserved for X11. Freedesktop
    GlobalShortcuts portal wires the toggle-quake id on KDE Plasma 6
    and xdg-desktop-portal-hyprland / -wlr with a 500ms debounce;
    in-app QShortcut fallback stays active on GNOME Shell.
  * Security: plugin capability audit UI renders every declared
    permission as a revocable checkbox under Settings → Plugins,
    persisted to config.plugin_grants[<name>] and applied on next
    plugin reload. Image-bomb defenses cap total decoded image bytes
    at 256 MB per terminal across Sixel / Kitty / iTerm2 OSC 1337;
    per-image MAX_IMAGE_DIM = 4096 dimension cap remains in place.
  * Distribution readiness (H1–H4): SECURITY.md (coordinated-
    disclosure policy with supported-versions table, reporting
    channel, timeline, severity rubric) + CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
    (Contributor Covenant 2.1) clear the Debian / Fedora / Ubuntu
    security-team review gate. AppStream metainfo + polished desktop
    entry with Desktop Actions for NewWindow + QuakeMode. groff -man
    man page at packaging/linux/ants-terminal.1 covering every CLI
    flag, environment variable, and exit status. Shell completions
    (bash / zsh / fish) installed to conventional vendor paths,
    auto-discovered on system-wide installs. CI runs appstreamcli
    validate --explain, desktop-file-validate, and groff -man lint
    on every push.
  * Dev experience: Project Audit gains new rules
    (unbounded_callback_payloads, qnetworkreply_no_abort,
    silent_catch, missing_build_flags, no_ci), fixture-per-check
    self-consistency enforcement (audit_fixture_coverage), and a
    build-asan CI lane running ctest + binary smoke under ASan/UBSan
