ants-terminal (0.6.29-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Status-bar reliability fixes: git branch chip no longer elides to
    "…" when there's plenty of space (ElidedLabel minimumSizeHint now
    reflects the full-text width, capped at maximumWidth, so short text
    always renders in full). Review Changes button refreshes on every
    2 s status tick and at startup — previously only tab-switch or
    Claude hooks refreshed it, so a dirty repo at launch stayed
    hidden. Add-to-allowlist button: both the scroll-scan and
    hook-server paths now share the same objectName so tab-switch
    cleanup catches both; saveSettings returns a bool and failures
    are surfaced in-UI instead of swallowed. Claude status label
    polls immediately on tab-switch (not 2 s later).
  * New tests/features/status_bar_elision feature test locks the
    short-text-never-elides invariant in a real QMainWindow +
    QStatusBar harness.

