ants-terminal (0.6.28-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * End-to-end feature review + status-bar overflow polish. New
    ElidedLabel widget caps the three status-bar text slots (git branch,
    transient message, foreground process) so long strings truncate with
    "…" instead of pushing sibling widgets off-screen. Same treatment
    applied to the window title-bar label, the "Claude: …" label, and
    the audit-dialog status label.
  * Quake-mode toggle no longer auto-hides the window 200 ms after a
    show toggle. The finished→hide() slot from the previous hide toggle
    persisted on the reused QPropertyAnimation; now disconnected before
    every start() and only re-attached on the hide branch.
  * Resize (both main-screen simple-copy and alt-screen paths) now
    preserves the per-line combining-char side table. Pre-0.6.28 every
    resize wiped accents / ZWJ / diacritics because the copy walked
    cells only. New tests/features/combining_on_resize feature test
    pins the behaviour — fails against pre-fix code, passes on fix.
  * Config + session writes now fsync the temp file before atomic
    rename, closing the kernel-crash data-loss window between close()
    and rename() on ext4 data=ordered.
  * Auto-profile rule regex compilation is cached across the 2 s
    poll tick (was recompiled per-rule per-tick), and invalid patterns
    are detected via QRegularExpression::isValid() and warned once
    instead of silently never matching.

 -- Anthony Schemel <aant.schemel@gmail.com>  Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

ants-terminal (0.6.26-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Ink-TUI overflow-repaint no longer wipes scrollback or duplicates
    the replay. CSI 2J followed within 50 ms by CSI 3J on the main
    screen (Ink's clearTerminal: CSI 2J + CSI 3J + CSI H + fullStatic
    + output) is now recognised as a frame-reset marker — scrollback
    is preserved and the 0.6.22 suppression window is armed for the
    incoming replay. Standalone CSI 3J still clears scrollback as the
    user explicitly requested. Two new conformance scenarios in
    tests/features/scrollback_redraw pin both behaviours.
  * Status bar is now height-consistent (32 px floor). Previously the
    bar grew when the transient "Add to allowlist" button appeared
    and shrank when it went away, because QStatusBar's size hint
    tracks its tallest child.
  * "Review Changes" button now matches sibling status-bar buttons
    via the global QPushButton stylesheet. The 0.6.26 "bold at 11 px
    to fix Gruvbox contrast" attempt produced squished small-caps
    rendering on Fusion + monospace. Distinct disabled state (dashed
    border + italic + muted fg) makes clean-repo visibility unambiguous.
  * Git-branch chip now has a vertical divider separating it from the
    transient-status slot, visible on every theme including the
    low-contrast ones where the chip treatment alone blended in.
  * Focus auto-returns to the active terminal when focus lands on
    chrome widgets with no dialog open — clicking a status bar
    button or closing a menu no longer parks keystrokes on the chrome.
  * Claude Code context-usage progress bar is hidden until a real
    non-zero percent arrives; fresh tabs no longer show a persistent
    0% widget.
  * Tab-colour badge replaced with a vertical gradient (transparent
    top → chosen colour bottom). Active-tab accent underline is
    preserved by excluding the bottom 2 px from the gradient area.

